.TH "smc_wr_tx_get_free_slot" 9 "smc_wr_tx_get_free_slot" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
smc_wr_tx_get_free_slot \- returns buffer for message assembly, and sets info for pending transmit tracking
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" smc_wr_tx_get_free_slot
.BI "(struct smc_link *link "  ","
.BI "smc_wr_tx_handler handler "  ","
.BI "struct smc_wr_buf **wr_buf "  ","
.BI "struct smc_rdma_wr **wr_rdma_buf "  ","
.BI "struct smc_wr_tx_pend_priv **wr_pend_priv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "link" 12
Pointer to smc_link used to later send the message.
.IP "handler" 12
Send completion handler function pointer.
.IP "wr_buf" 12
Out value returns pointer to message buffer.
.IP "wr_rdma_buf" 12
Out value returns pointer to rdma work request.
.IP "wr_pend_priv" 12
Out value returns pointer serving as handler context.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or -errno on error.
